                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday I again impressed upon British minister for foreign affairs injustice
                    and objection able nature of provision requiring previous notice to sealing
                    vessels. Last night in debate attorney-general said clause <pb facs="0178"
                        n="172" xml:id="pg_172"/> had been entirely misunderstood in the United
                    States, and declared imperial obligation was imposed on Great Britain, and if
                    Canada should not consent still Imperial Government would loyally carry award
                    info effect. Leaders of opposition join with Government in declaring honor Of
                    the country involved in carrying out award. The text of the act of Congress has
                    been received.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
